[Vampire bat transmitted rabies is a sporadic problem throughout the
tropical Americas. Bovine and equine animals are the preferred hosts
for this bat, but there are occasional human cases, as has been the
case in Amazonas of neighboring Peru in February and March of this
year (2011) (see ProMED-mail no 20110312.0799). Vaccination of cattle
and horses against rabies is prudent and cost effective.

An image of the vampire bat, _Desmodus rotundus_, can be accessed at
http://www.animalpicturesarchive.com/WebImg/335/1208760244-t.jpg.

An interactive HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Ecuador can be accessed
at http://healthmap.org/r/0YRY. - Mod.TY]
